http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Hawaii Content and Performance Standards for Health

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The Health standards provide a coherent, professionally defensible rationale for health education. They provide clarity of purpose, set high and challenging expectations for all students, and ensure that Health Education is emphasized from kindergarten through the twelfth grade. The standards do not prescribe a particular curriculum, nor do they subscribe to any one method or approach to teaching. They serve as a map for schools to develop their own framework from which teachers can examine and improve their teaching and students' learning.
Core Concepts — Understand concepts related to health promotion and disease prevention
Mental and Emotional Health
Describe appropriate ways to express feelings
Describe the relationship between physical and emotional health
Explain the relationship between mental, emotional, social, and physical health
Compare the relationships among mental, emotional, social, and physical health in adulthood
Healthy Eating and Physical Activity
Explain the benefits associated with exercise
Describe the benefits associated with a healthy diet
Describe the importance of physical activity and exercise as part of a healthy lifestyle
Explain the importance of a healthy diet as part of a healthy lifestyle
Describe short- and long-term effects and consequences of poor nutrition and lack of physical activity
Promoting Safety and Preventing Violence and Unintentional Injury
Describe barriers and situations that are safe, risky, or harmful to self and others
Describe how to assess situations that might be dangerous or risky and strategies to avoid such situations
Describe short- and long-term effects and consequences of violent or aggressive behaviors
Describe types and degrees of risk encountered in daily living and formulate strategies to avoid or reduce threatening situations
Know how to use appropriate strategies to avoid, reduce, and report threatening situations
Personal Health and Wellness
Describe how individuals can promote and protect their own health
Describe helpful and harmful substances and their proper use
Describe the benefits associated with personal cleanliness
Describe the signs and symptoms of common illness and strategies one can use to avoid spreading or catching illnesses
Describe the relationship between health behaviors and well-being
Explain the consequences associated with exposure to environmental elements
Explain the importance of early detection and treatment of disease
Describe the body system functions, how they interact with each other, and how they are impacted by health behaviors
Identify choices individuals can make to promote or harm their health
Identify proper health care and describe how it can prevent premature death and disability
Identify personal health behaviors and other factors that impact body system functions
Explain the purpose of public health policies and government regulations in health
Tobacco-Free Lifestyle
Identify the consequences of using tobacco products
Describe short- and long-term effects and consequences of tobacco product use
Alcohol and Other Drugfree Lifestyle
Identify the consequences of alcohol and drug abuse
Describe short- and long-term effects and consequences of drinking alcohol and using drugs
Sexual Health and Responsibility
Identify the stages of growth and development in humans related to puberty and adolescence
Describe short- and long-term effects and consequences of sexual activity
Accessing Information — Access valid health information and health-promoting products and services
Health Information, Products, and Services Across Topic Areas
Name people in the school and community who provide health support for others
Explain where health information can be found in the home, school, and community
Identify the characteristics of valid health information, products, and services
Identify when it is necessary to access health services for self and others
Use appropriate sources to access valid health information, products, and services
Compare health information provided from home, school, and community resources
Evaluate the validity of different sources of health information
Describe when and how to access health services for self and others
Self-Management — Practice health-enhancing behaviors and reduce health risks
Mental and Emotional Health
Describe personal stressors and ways to deal with stressful situations
Use appropriate strategies for dealing with emotional and stressful situations
Explain personal preferences for coping and stress management strategies
Compare a variety of personal coping and stress management strategies
Personal Health and Wellness
Evaluate behaviors that are safe, risky, or harmful to self and others
Explain the importance of assuming responsibility for personal health behaviors
Compare the importance of enhancing health and safety in the community, workplace, and/or at home
Evaluate personal behaviors within the risk areas (e.g., tobacco use, alcohol and drug use, nutrition, fitness, personal safety, sexual activity)
Analyzing Influences — Understand the influences of culture, family, peers, media, technology, and other factors on health
Factors Influencing Health Across Topic Areas
Describe internal (e.g., one's own feelings, moods, curiosity, physical well-being) and external (e.g., family, school, media) factors that influence health behaviors
Identify internal and external factors that influence health behaviors and health-related decisions
Explain the influence of internal and external factors on health outcomes
Evaluate the interrelationship of internal and external factors that influence health behaviors
Interpersonal Communication — Use interpersonal communication skills to enhance health
Communication Skils Across Topic Areas
Use effective verbal and nonverbal communication
Use effective and appropriate ways to express feelings, wants, and needs
Describe basic refusal skills
Describe how to be a good friend and responsible family member
Use appropriate strategies for effective verbal and nonverbal communication in formal and informal settings
Use strategies to avoid inappropriate communication (e.g., name-calling, put-downs, and harassment)
Use effective verbal and non-verbal communication skills
Use effective behaviors that communicate care, consideration, and respect of self and others
Know how to use appropriate verbal and non-verbal communication skills that are necessary to avoid potentially harmful situations
Promoting Safety and Preventing Violence and Unintentional Injury
Know how to use appropriate non-violent strategies to deal with conflict and dispute
Identify possible causes of disputes connected to personal, family, and community matters
Apply appropriate conflict resolution strategies to deal with potentially harmful situations
Know how to use appropriate strategies to resolve disagreements
Decision-Making and Goal-Setting — Use decision-making and goal-setting skills to enhance health
Decision-Making Across Topic Areas
Explain when and who to ask for help in making health-related decisions and setting goals
Identify the elements of a decision-making model related to health issues and problems
Evaluate decisions made on health issues and problems
Describe decision-making processes related to healthrelated decisions
Assess health-related decisions for consequences that affect oneself and others
Explain decision-making strategies used to make health-related decisions
Evaluate health decisions that have immediate and long-term consequences on the individual, family, and community
Know how to apply appropriate responses to risky situations
Goal-Setting Across Topic Areas
Name a personal health goal and describe a plan to achieve it
Identify appropriate goal-setting strategies to set personal health goals
Evaluate personal health strengths and risks to set personal goals
Create and implement a plan for enhancing life-long goals
Advocacy — Advocate for personal, family, and community health
Advocacy Across Topic Areas
Describe ways to help others promote and protect their own health
Name people or groups that advocate for healthy individuals, families, and communities
Use appropriate strategies to express individual opinions about health issues
Use effective strategies to influence and support others in making healthful choices
Use appropriate methods to communicate accurate health information and ideas
Describe how barriers can affect the communication of information, ideas, feelings, and opinions
Use effective strategies to help others promote and protect their health
Design a school-wide health advocacy campaign that advocates for a healthy lifestyle
Evaluate the effectiveness of strategies in communicating health information
Explain how health messages can be translated to particular audiences
